article.description: Richmond Aririguzoh registered 13 points and three assists as Princeton routed Dartmouth 66-44 on Friday night.
article.headline: Aririguzoh leads Princeton over Dartmouth 66-44
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Richmond Aririguzoh registered 13 points and three assists as Princeton routed Dartmouth 66-44 on Friday night. Ryan Schwieger had 12 points for Princeton (8-8, 3-0 Ivy League), which earned its fifth consecutive victory. Ethan Wright added eight rebounds. Dartmouth totaled 17 first-half points, a season low for the team. Trevon Ary-Turner had 11 points for the Big Green (7-11, 0-3), who have now lost six games in a row. Chris Knight added 10 points. Princeton plays Harvard at home on Saturday.
